Employment Agreement

I. Proprietary and Confidential Information
During employment, Employee will receive access to proprietary and confidential information (“Confidential Information”). Employee shall not disclose such information to third parties and shall use it solely to perform assigned duties for the Company on a need-to-know basis.

II. Exclusions
The obligations in Section I do not apply to information that (a) is public through no fault of Employee; (b) was known to Employee prior to disclosure; (c) is independently developed without using Company information; or (d) must be disclosed as required by law, subpoena, or court order.

III. Return and Deletion of Materials
At the end of employment or upon Company’s request, Employee will promptly return or destroy all materials containing Confidential Information, including copies and backups, and will certify destruction upon request.

IV. Remedies
Employee acknowledges that breach of Sections I–III may cause immediate and irreparable harm to the Company for which monetary damages are inadequate. The Company shall be entitled to equitable relief, including temporary and permanent injunctive relief, without the necessity of posting bond.

V. Governing Law
This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the State of New York, without regard to conflicts of laws rules. Venue and jurisdiction shall lie exclusively in New York County, New York.
